sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor Admin
    participant MSS as McpServersSection<br/>useMcpServers hook
    participant Dialog as McpServerFormDialog<br/>AllowedToolsSelector
    participant API as AugmentApi<br/>adminEndpoints
    participant BE as augment-backend
    participant MTS as McpTestService<br/>mcpClient.ts
    participant ACS as AdminConfigService<br/>augment_admin_config DB
    participant RCR as RuntimeConfigResolver<br/>mergeMcpServers
    participant SS as StatusService<br/>checkMcpServerHealth
    participant ExtMCP as External MCP Server

    rect rgb(254, 243, 199)
        Note over Admin,ACS: Phase 1 - Load Configuration
        MSS->>API: useAdminConfig('mcpServers')
        API->>BE: GET /admin/config/mcpServers
        BE->>ACS: get('mcpServers')
        ACS-->>BE: DB overrides (or null)
        BE-->>MSS: Admin-added servers

        MSS->>API: useAdminConfig('disabledMcpServerIds')
        API->>BE: GET /admin/config/disabledMcpServerIds
        BE->>ACS: get('disabledMcpServerIds')
        ACS-->>MSS: Disabled YAML server IDs

        MSS->>API: useStatus()
        API->>BE: GET /status
        BE->>RCR: mergeMcpServers()
        Note over RCR: YAML baseline +<br/>DB overrides +<br/>filter disabled IDs
        RCR->>SS: checkMcpServerHealth(effectiveServers)
        loop For each effective MCP server
            SS->>ExtMCP: MCP SDK connect + listTools
            ExtMCP-->>SS: Tool schemas or error
        end
        SS-->>BE: MCPServerStatus[]
        BE-->>MSS: { mcpServers: [{connected, toolCount, tools, source}] }
    end

    rect rgb(209, 250, 229)
        Note over Admin,ExtMCP: Phase 2 - Add New MCP Server
        Admin->>MSS: Click "Add Server"
        MSS->>Dialog: Open McpServerFormDialog

        Admin->>Dialog: Enter server details
        Note over Dialog: Fields:<br/>- ID (auto or manual)<br/>- Name<br/>- Type (streamable-http / sse)<br/>- URL<br/>- Bearer token (optional)<br/>- Require approval toggle

        Admin->>Dialog: Click "Test Connection"
        Dialog->>API: testMcpConnection(url, type, headers)
        API->>BE: POST /admin/mcp/test-connection
        BE->>MTS: testConnection(url, type, headers)
        MTS->>MTS: SSRF check (isPrivateUrlWithDns)
        MTS->>ExtMCP: MCP SDK StreamableHTTPClientTransport
        ExtMCP-->>MTS: Connection + tool list
        MTS-->>BE: { success, tools: string[] }
        BE-->>Dialog: Test result

        alt Test successful
            Dialog->>Dialog: Show AllowedToolsSelector
            Note over Dialog: Checkboxes for discovered tools<br/>Default: all selected<br/>Deselect to restrict
            Admin->>Dialog: Select allowed tools
            Admin->>Dialog: Click "Add"
            Dialog-->>MSS: New server added to local state
        else Test failed
            Dialog->>Dialog: Show error message
        end
    end

    rect rgb(224, 231, 255)
        Note over Admin,ACS: Phase 3 - Save Configuration
        Admin->>MSS: Click "Save"
        MSS->>API: save(adminServers)
        API->>BE: PUT /admin/config/mcpServers
        BE->>ACS: set('mcpServers', servers)
        ACS->>ACS: Upsert to augment_admin_config

        MSS->>API: save(disabledIds)
        API->>BE: PUT /admin/config/disabledMcpServerIds
        BE->>ACS: set('disabledMcpServerIds', ids)
        ACS-->>MSS: Saved

        Note over MSS: Next status poll picks up<br/>new effective configuration
    end

    rect rgb(237, 233, 254)
        Note over Admin,MSS: Phase 4 - Manage Existing Servers
        alt Edit server
            Admin->>MSS: Click edit on McpServerCard
            MSS->>Dialog: Pre-fill form with existing config
            Admin->>Dialog: Modify + re-test + save
        else Disable YAML server
            Admin->>MSS: Toggle off a YAML-sourced server
            MSS->>MSS: Add ID to disabledMcpServerIds
        else Remove admin server
            Admin->>MSS: Click delete on admin-added server
            MSS->>MSS: Remove from local adminServers
        else Reset all overrides
            Admin->>MSS: Click "Reset"
            MSS->>API: delete('mcpServers')
            MSS->>API: delete('disabledMcpServerIds')
            Note over MSS: Reverts to YAML-only configuration
        end
    end

    rect rgb(254, 226, 226)
        Note over RCR,ExtMCP: Runtime - Chat Tool Resolution
        Note over RCR: On each chat request:<br/>RuntimeConfigResolver.mergeMcpServers()
        RCR->>RCR: YAML + DB overrides - disabled
        alt Direct mode (default)
            RCR->>RCR: Pass MCP server configs to Llama Stack
            Note over ExtMCP: Llama Stack connects directly<br/>to MCP servers
        else Backend mode
            RCR->>RCR: BackendToolExecutor connects via MCP SDK
            RCR->>ExtMCP: Connect + discover + execute tool calls
        end
    end
